    "body": "> The `starship explain` command may be useful to you. Besides that, you may wish to use the [plain text symbols preset](https://starship.rs/presets/plain-text).\n\nYes, thanks a lot. When I read about `starship explain`, I compartmentalized it as only a debugging tool, but it makes sense for this purpose as well. That preset is good to know - it is what I ended up doing with my own script - except that I combine both : \n1. The \"at a glance\" nature of icons one is familiar with - we can even identify icons in peripheral vision or from a distance.\n2. The textual explanation if one is not familiar with the icon.",
